    "Graph pooling methods have achieved remarkable success in various applications, but they still face several challenges that hinder their widespread adoption.",
    "These challenges include robustness, explainability, expressive ability, computational efficiency, generalizability, dynamic graph processing, large-scale graph processing, and hyperparametric sensitivity.",
    "Addressing these challenges is crucial to unlocking the full potential of graph pooling methods and enabling their application in real-world scenarios.",
    "Table 8 summarizes the challenges and opportunities of the graph pooling methods.",
    "In the real world, much data exists in the form of graph structures, which may have phenomena such as the adding and deleting of nodes as well as the adding and decreasing of edges."
